300 g Tilapia
1 unit(s) Lemon
170 g Orzo
113 g Sugar Snap Peas
7 g Dill
113 g Baby Tomatoes
2 unit(s) Garlic, cloves
1 tsp Garlic Salt
0.13 tsp Pepper*
1 tsp Oil*
0.13 tsp Salt*
1 tbsp Unsalted Butter*

Add 6 cups water and 1 tsp salt to a medium pot (use same for 4 ppl). Cover and bring to a boil over high heat.
Roughly chop half the dill (all for 4 ppl).
Zest, then juice half the lemon (whole lemon for 4 ppl). Cut any remaining lemon into wedges.
Peel, then mince or grate garlic.

Add snap peas, tomatoes, 1 tsp oil (dbl for 4 ppl) and half the garlic to a parchment-lined baking sheet. Season with salt and pepper, then toss to combine.
Roast in the middle of the oven until veggies are tender-crisp, 8-10 min.

Meanwhile, add orzo to the boiling water. Cook uncovered, stirring occasionally, until tender, 6-8 min.
Reserve 2 tbsp pasta water (dbl for 4 ppl), then drain and return orzo to the same pot, off heat.

Meanwhile, pat tilapia dry with paper towels. Sprinkle lemon zest over top, then season with half the garlic salt and pepper.
Heat a large non-stick pan over medium heat.
When hot, add 1/2 tbsp butter (dbl for 4 ppl), then tilapia. Pan-fry until golden-brown and cooked through, 2-3 min per side. **

Add reserved pasta water, dill, remaining garlic, remaining garlic salt, 1 tbsp lemon juice and 1/2 tbsp butter (dbl both for 4 ppl) to orzo.
Season with pepper, then stir to combine.

Divide orzo, tilapia and roasted veggies between plates.
Squeeze a lemon wedge over top, if desired.

If you've opted to get tilapia, season it in the same way the recipe instructs you to season the salmon. Cook tilapia until golden-brown and cooked through, 2-3 min per side.**